{"word":"πλοῖον","slug":"πλοῖον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>πλοῖον, ου, τό</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πλέω\">πλέω</a></el>] of a seafaring vessel <b>ship <a href='B:510 20:13'>Ac 20:13</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in Ac; <b><a href='B:660 3:4'>Js 3:4</a>; <a href='B:730 8:9'>Rv 8:9</a>; <a href='B:730 18:19'>18:19</a>.</b> In the gospels always of a relatively small vessel used on Lake Gennesaret generally for fishing,<b>boat <a href='B:470 4:21'>Mt 4:21</a>; <a href='B:480 4:1'>Mk 4:1</a>; <a href='B:490 5:2'>Lk 5:2f</a>; <a href='B:500 6:19'>J 6:19</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:πλοιάριον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:πλοκή\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}